To measure the salience of climate-related risks, we follow Zander and Garnett (2020) in asking respondents to assess the relative salience of a variety of factors (e.g., health, access to labor, weather conditions) to their livelihood decision-making through the question: “How significant would you say [X factor] has been in determining your level of economic success from growing crops?” We then calculate the salience of climate-related risks (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
